data.enText: very stupid; not able to understand or to do sth
data.chText: 很愚蠢的；（对某事）不懂的，无能的

tr: totally uninformed about what is going on
not having even a clue from which to infer what is occurring

example.ex: I came into adult life clueless about a lot of things that most people take for granted...
example.tran: 我已成年，却对许多大部分人认为理所当然的事情一窍不通。

example.ex: We have found some drivers clueless as to the law.
example.tran: 我们发现有些司机对这一法规一无所知。

value.def: If you describe someone as clueless, you are showing your disapproval of the fact that they do not know anything about a particular subject or that they are incapable of doing a particular thing properly.
value.tran: 一无所知的;一窍不通的
